<p>This building, at <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Galip%C3%A1n+La+Latina/@40.4115406,-3.7111639,3a,75y,43.39h,93.29t/data=!3m7!1e1!3m5!1snNMjrelB1OqVbfsJ4FnM9g!2e0!6shttps:%2F%2Fstreetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com%2Fv1%2Fthumbnail%3Fcb_client%3Dmaps_sv.tactile%26w%3D900%26h%3D600%26pitch%3D-3.2900000000000063%26panoid%3DnNMjrelB1OqVbfsJ4FnM9g%26yaw%3D43.39!7i16384!8i8192!4m7!3m6!1s0xd4227d7cbdf69b1:0x1f7c976c79f17cf9!8m2!3d40.4116943!4d-3.7109675!10e5!16s%2Fg%2F11g7czvtt2?entry=ttu&#038;g_ep=EgoyMDI1MDYyOS4wIKXMDSoASAFQAw%3D%3D">1643 Plaza de los Carros</a> in Madrid, is half illusion &#8212; the façade on the left, including the windows, ironwork, awnings, even the residents, is all a <em>trompe-l&#8217;œil</em> mural by artist Alberto Pirrongelli.</p>
